# StackedPageMessages

If you intend to display a stacked page message after page load, for screen readers to announce the change, make sure the page message is rendered in a page region with `aria-live=“assertive”` or `role="alert"`.
Once a page message in stacked page message is closed, the focus should move to the next page message or next focusable element on the page.

Page messages within the Stacked Page Message will be sitting inside a landmark:

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/stacked-page-messages
```

```tsx
import { StackedPageMessages } from '@ids-ts/stacked-page-messages';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Test Automation ID. |
| `children` | `React.ReactElement | React.ReactElement[]` | No | Page Messages |
| `onClose` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | Callback when component is closed. |
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface StackedPageMessagesProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** Test Automation ID. */
  automationId?: string;
  /** Page Messages */
  children?: React.ReactElement | React.ReactElement[];
  /** Callback when component is closed. */
  onClose?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /**
   * Whether component is open.
   *
   * @default true
   */
  open: boolean;
}
```

</details>

